{{Expand German|date=January 2011|Deutsche Fotothek}}
[[File:Deutsche Fotothek Logo 2012.svg|right|200px|Deutsche Fotothek logo]]
The '''Deutsche Fotothek''' ({{IPA-de|ˈdɔʏtʃə fotoˈteːk}}) is a [[picture library]] in [[Dresden]], [[Germany]], located in the [[Saxon State Library]]. It holds more than two million images. Its strengths are in art, architecture, music, geography, technology, the economy, and the [[Saxony]] region.  Its collection came from institutions, companies and individuals such as [[Hermann Krone]].

== Wikimedia Commons image donation ==

In 2009, the library announced that it was donating approximately 250,000 image files to [[Wikimedia Commons]] under a [[Creative Commons]] BY-SA 3.0 license.<ref>PRESS INFO, Berlin, March 31, 2009, Meeting Point Wikipedia</ref><ref>[http://www.slub-dresden.de/fileadmin/groups/homepage/Aktuelles/Wikimedia.pdf Press release]{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Deutsche Fotothek, March 31, 2009</ref>

